The paper focuses on designing an in-memory key-value store that uses erasure coding to achieve high availability and fast recovery while keeping low data redundancy across storage servers. This topic is closely related to distributed systems (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of coordinated requests in degraded mode, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
